OL,3,C'It was inhumane': Daughter slams
OL,4,Cprison after mum neglected and left to
OL,5,Csuffer
OL,7,FFollowing the two week-long inquest, a
OL,8,Fjury returned a conclusion of suicide
OL,9,Fcontributed to by neglect - defined as
OL,10,Fa gross failure in basic care and
OL,11,Fattention.
OL,13,FMany of the jurors were in tears as
OL,14,Fthe foreperson read out their findings
OL,15,Fat Coroner's Court.
OL,17,FThey found there were failings in
OL,18,Fcommunication and information sharing
OL,19,Fbetween health care staff and prison
OL,20,Fstaff which contributed "more than
OL,21,Fminimally" to Christine's death.
